instructions: Soak the dried chickpeas in water overnight.
The next day, drain the chickpeas and rinse them well.
Remove the stems from the parsley and cilantro, and chop the leaves.

In a food processor, combine the chickpeas, onion, garlic, parsley, cilantro, cumin, coriander, salt, black pepper, and baking soda. Process until you have a fine, slightly sticky mixture. If needed, add a little bit of water.
